testprocedure.test-case-summary: This test procedure is called by a test case and is used to verify the SUTs support of the dlDetectorDataSubscription dialog as an OC using variables provided by the calling test case. This procedure supports verification of requirements related to user need 2.3.7.1.1 [Need for Direct Measurements of Traffic Flow and Conditions] and is used for both valid and invalid test cases.

testStep.functionId: Step 1 CONFIGURE: Determine the Application Layer Standard that will be used for this test. RECORD this information as: ApplicationLayerStandard: ${ApplicationLayerStandard}

Step 2 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Restrictions is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R473_Restrictions_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R473_Restrictions_Supported}

Step 3 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Owner Organization is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.2). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R474_Owner_Organization_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R474_Owner_Organization_Supported}

Step 4 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Detector Station is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.3). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R475_Detector_Station_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R475_Detector_Station_Supported}

Step 5 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Data Collection Start is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.4). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R476_Data_Collection_Start_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R476_Data_Collection_Start_Supported}

Step 6 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Data Collection End is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.5). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R477_Data_Collection_End_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R477_Data_Collection_End_Supported}

Step 7 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Data Type is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.6). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R478_Data_Type_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R478_Data_Type_Supported}

Step 8 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Average Vehicle Speed is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.7). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R479_Average_Vehicle_Speed_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R479_Average_Vehicle_Speed_Supported}

Step 9 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Average Vehicle Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.8). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R480_Average_Vehicle_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R480_Average_Vehicle_Queue_Supported}

Step 10 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Stops is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.9). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R481_Vehicle_Stops_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R481_Vehicle_Stops_Supported}

Step 11 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Count - Bin 1 is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.10). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R482_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_1_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R482_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_1_Supported}

Step 12 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Count - Bin 2 is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.11). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R483_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_2_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R483_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_2_Supported}

Step 13 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Count - Bin 3 is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.12). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R484_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_3_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R484_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_3_Supported}

Step 14 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Count - Bin 4 is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.13). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R485_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_4_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R485_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_4_Supported}

Step 15 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Vehicle Count - Bin 5 is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.6.2.3.5.2.14). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N104R486_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_5_Supported = ${TMDD_N104R486_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_5_Supported}
Step 16 CONFIGURE: Determine the number of publication message transmissions that will be received within this test. RECORD this information as: PublicationsToReceive: ${PublicationsToReceive}
Step 17 CONFIGURE: Determine whether an error response message is expected for this test. RECORD this information as: PublicationErrorResponseExpected: ${PublicationErrorResponseExpected}

Step 18 CONFIGURE: IF PublicationErrorResponseExpected is true, determine the expected error code response for this test. RECORD this information as: PublicationErrorTypeExpected: ${PublicationErrorTypeExpected}
Step 19 CONFIGURE: Define the publication response message that will be sent to the SUT. RECORD this information as: PublicationResponseMessage: ${PublicationResponseMessage}
Step 20 CONFIGURE: Determine whether the Authentication parameters need to be verified within this test. RECORD this information as: AuthenticationCheck: ${AuthenticationCheck}
Step 21 CONFIGURE: Determine whether the SUT will be allowed access to the information requested in this test. RECORD this information as: AllowAccess: ${AllowAccess}
Step 22 CONFIGURE: Define the publication message that will be sent to the SUT. RECORD this information as: SubscriptionMessage: ${SubscriptionMessage}
Step 23 CONFIGURE: Determine whether an error response message is expected for this test. RECORD this information as: SubscriptionErrorResponseExpected: ${SubscriptionErrorResponseExpected}

Step 24 CONFIGURE: IF SubscriptionErrorResponseExpected is true, determine the expected error code response for this test. RECORD this information as: SubscriptionErrorTypeExpected: ${SubscriptionErrorTypeExpected}

Step 25 SUBSCRIPTION-EC with the following parameters: DIALOG=dlDetectorDataSubscription SUBSCRIPTIONMESSAGE = SubscriptionMessage SUBSCRIPTIONERRORRESPONSEEXPECTED = SubscriptionErrorResponseExpected SUBSCRIPTIONERRORTYPEEXPECTED = SubscriptionErrorTypeExpected Returns: CONTINUEPUBLICATION
Step 26 IF SubscriptionErrorResponseExpected is not equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE, OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1 WHILE CONTINUEPUBLICATION is equal to TRUE then CONTINUE, OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.

Step 26.1.1 PUBLICATION-EC-RECEIVE with the following parameters: DIALOG=dlDetectorDataUpdate PUBLICATIONSTORECEIVE = PublicationsToReceive PUBLICATIONERRORRESPONSEEXPECTED = PublicationErrorResponseExpected PUBLICATIONERRORTYPEEXPECTED = PublicationErrorTypeExpected AUTHENTICATIONCHECK = AuthenticationCheck ALLOWACCESS = AllowAccess Returns: CONTINUEPUBLICATION
Step 26.1.2 IF PublicationErrorResponseExpected is not equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE, OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.1 IF TMDD_N104R473_Restrictions_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.1.1 VERIFY that element restrictions exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item
Step 26.1.2.2 IF TMDD_N104R474_Owner_Organization_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.2.1 VERIFY that element station-id exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.2.2 VERIFY that element station-id exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.3 IF TMDD_N104R475_Detector_Station_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.3.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-count exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.4 IF TMDD_N104R476_Data_Collection_Start_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.4.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-occupancy exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.5 IF TMDD_N104R477_Data_Collection_End_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.5.1 VERIFY that element start-time exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.6 IF TMDD_N104R478_Data_Type_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.6.1 VERIFY that element end-time exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.7 IF TMDD_N104R479_Average_Vehicle_Speed_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.7.1 VERIFY that element detector-data-type exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.8 IF TMDD_N104R480_Average_Vehicle_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.8.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-speed exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.9 IF TMDD_N104R481_Vehicle_Stops_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.9.1 VERIFY that element queue-length exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.10 IF TMDD_N104R482_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_1_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.10.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-stops exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.11 IF TMDD_N104R483_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_2_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.11.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-count-bin1 exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.12 IF TMDD_N104R484_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_3_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.12.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-count-bin2 exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.13 IF TMDD_N104R485_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_4_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.13.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-count-bin3 exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.14 IF TMDD_N104R486_Vehicle_Count_-_Bin_5_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 26.1.2.14.1 VERIFY that element vehicle-count-bin4 exists within each instance of detectorDataMsg.detector-data-item.detector-list.detector-data-detail
Step 26.1.2.15 VERIFY that the values within the REQUEST message are correct per the TMDD standard and known operational conditions.
